12.40	Acids	Acid	An acid (from the Latin acidus/acÄ“re meaning sour) is a substance which reacts with a base. Commonly, acids can be identified as tasting sour, reacting with metals such as calcium, and bases like sodium carbonate. Aqueous acids have a pH of less than 7, where an acid of lower pH is typically stronger. Chemicals or substances having the property of an acid are said to be acidic.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Zn_reaction_with_HCl.JPG/220px-Zn_reaction_with_HCl.JPG
